node.text:
Arizona has been my home for 17 years now and as a father and local business owner, I'm heart broken to see the impact COVID-19 is having throughout our community.  Despite the adversity, I remain optimistic knowing the resolve of the people of AZ, who like me, are steadfast in the commitment to recharge this city when the time is right.  Presently, our focus should be on the health and caretaking of one another.  Please take this seriously, stay inside and keep your distance.  To the first responders, doctors, nurses, EMTs, firemen, grocery workers, truck drivers, delivery people, and cleaning staff,  I want to extend my gratitude for your heroic work by being on the front lines everyday fighting to save lives.  We need to rally behind all of them and cheer them on.

Care for one another. Lead with kindness. We’re all in this together.

It’s been an honor these last few days to work with my friends at @gobellbanks, @InterlachenCC, and four world class chefs from the Twin Cities @chefjustinsutherland @gavinkaysen @christinanguyenmpls & @yiayang70 in support of causes that are transforming my hometown.

Thank you to The African American Breast Cancer Alliance, The Larry & Pamela McKenzie Athletic Life Skills Center at North High School, @boysandgirlsclubstc @childrensmn & @bigtwyncities...your impact on our community is immeasurable. I am so inspired by your work. Keep leading by example 🙏🏾

Photos: @uzomaobasi

node.text: This Memorial Day, I’m remembering my grandfather, Dr. Robert Johnson, who was a lieutenant in the U.S. Army and received a Purple Heart for his service in the Korean War. 🙏🏾 #USAApartner I’m planting a poppy flower in remembrance of my grandfather, which represents military members who died while serving our country. Thank you @USAA for giving me a poppy kit to honor my grandfather, and all the men and women who have served our country. #HonorThroughAction

They will always be with us through their lessons and love.
